Reasoning: The paper proposes a novel cooperative non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) system and investigates its performance in different scenarios. The paper focuses on communication and networking aspects, including relaying, outage probability, ergodic rate, and energy efficiency. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves system design and optimization, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses communication protocols and techniques, which could fall under cs.COMM (Computer Communications and Networks) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
